parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to jam or fail to latch, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle release button breaks
the buckle jams
the buckle is hard to insert
the buckle sticks when trying to unlatch
the seat belt strap breaks upon impact
the seat belt will not retract
the seat belt buckle is broken
unable to latch buckle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to fail to retract, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt will not retract
the driver's side lap/shoulder belt will not retract
the rear lap belt will not fasten.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dealerships to service vehicles under recall can lead to delays and inconvenience for consumers, potentially increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Dealerships refuse to service vehicles under recall
parts are not available
loaner cars are not provided
repairs are refused due to VIN or manufacturing date.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause electrical shorts, overheating, and fires, which can lead to vehicle damage, injury, or even death.
symptoms: The ignition switch sticks
the key cannot be released
the steering column cover begins smoking
the wiring under the hood catches on fire
the starter catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical issues in the steering column can cause fires, overheating, and smoking, which can lead to vehicle damage, injury, or even death.
symptoms: The steering column cover begins smoking
the ignition switch overheats
the wiring under the hood catches on fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat screw can cause the seat to become unstable or move unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents or injuries, especially during sudden stops or turns.
symptoms: The front seat screw falls out
the front seat becomes loose or unstable
the front seat does not stay in position
the front seat moves unexpectedly while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front passenger seat latch can cause the seat to become unstable or move unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents or injuries, especially during sudden stops or turns.
symptoms: The front passenger seat will not latch in a position
the front passenger seat becomes loose or unstable
the front passenger seat does not stay in position
the front passenger seat moves unexpectedly while driving.
